### **ACTION REQUIRED: CORRECT NGINX WORDPRESS CONFIGURATION**

#### **Step 1: Connect to Your VM**

*   **Action:** Please connect to your `browser-use-server` VM using the **Google Cloud Console "SSH" button**.

#### **Step 2: Open the Nginx Configuration File**

*   **Action:** Once you are in the VM's terminal, execute the following command. This will open the site's configuration file in the `nano` text editor.

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
```

#### **Step 3: Replace the Configuration**

*   **Action:**
    1.  Inside the `nano` editor, delete all the text that is currently in the file.
    2.  Copy the **entire, corrected configuration block** below and paste it into the empty `nano` window.

    ```nginx
    # Correct Nginx Configuration for pixelcartelhq.com (WordPress)

    server {
        listen 80;
        server_name pixelcartelhq.com www.pixelcartelhq.com m.pixelcartelhq.com;
        # This block is now handled by Certbot's auto-redirect
        return 301 https://$host$request_uri;
    }

    server {
        listen 443 ssl http2;
        server_name pixelcartelhq.com www.pixelcartelhq.com;

        # Define the root directory for WordPress files
        root /home/pixelcartelhq/htdocs/pixelcartelhq.com/wordpress;
        index index.php;

        # SSL Configuration managed by Certbot
        ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/pixelcartelhq.com/fullchain.pem;
        ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/pixelcartelhq.com/privkey.pem;
        include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf;
        ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem;

        location / {
            # This is the crucial part for WordPress URLs to work
            try_files $uri $uri/ /index.php?$args;
        }

        location ~ \.php$ {
            include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
            # Ensure this path is correct for your PHP version
            fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php/php8.2-fpm.sock;
        }

        location ~ /\.ht {
            deny all;
        }
    }

    server {
        listen 443 ssl http2;
        server_name m.pixelcartelhq.com;

        # Define the root directory for Mautic files
        root /home/pixelcartelhq/htdocs/pixelcartelhq.com/mautic;
        index index.php index.html;

        # SSL Configuration managed by Certbot
        ssl_certificate /etc/letsencrypt/live/pixelcartelhq.com/fullchain.pem;
        ssl_certificate_key /etc/letsencrypt/live/pixelcartelhq.com/privkey.pem;
        include /etc/letsencrypt/options-ssl-nginx.conf;
        ssl_dhparam /etc/letsencrypt/ssl-dhparams.pem;

        location / {
            try_files $uri /index.php?$args;
        }

        location ~ \.php$ {
            include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
            fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php/php8.2-fpm.sock;
        }
    }
    ```
    3.  Save the file and exit `nano` by pressing `Ctrl + X`, then `Y`, then `Enter`.

#### **Step 4: Test and Reload Nginx**

*   **Action:** Run the following commands in your VM terminal to test the new configuration and apply it.

```bash
# Test the new configuration for syntax errors
sudo nginx -t

# If the test is successful, gracefully reload Nginx
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

*   **Verification:** After reloading, open your browser and try navigating to **[https://pixelcartelhq.com/wp-admin/](https://pixelcartelhq.com/wp-admin/)** again. It should now load the WordPress login page correctly.

